it is illegal to scan your hard drive and transmit data back<br>
*****<br>
<br>
There is no such law.  The Hollings bill has not passed, and faces significant technical challenges to passing.  It is unlikely that in its current form it will pass.  For that matter, it doesn't even have provisions in it about local asset scanning, quite the contrary - it's a DRM bill aimed at protecting copyrighted assets (heatedly debated on it's focus towards implementation of this protection).  <br>
<br>
By clicking &quot;I accept&quot;, you do accept, and you are bound by the license.  You may choose to refuse at any time, or terminate the license contract, if you do not agree to its terms.<br>
<br>
VI is within its rights to condition your use of its software with permission to scan your local assets.  It could be scanning for porn, it doesn't matter - what matters is that it is within its bounds to put that rider into its EULA, and terminate the license if its conditions are violated.<br>
<br>
